{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review note (G6): The S1 caching substrate (anthropic system-prompt + tool-definition caching applied at the shared runner seam, gated to anthropic providers, no RunRequest content-list change) appears to ALREADY EXIST in the live code as story 0250 — see runner.py:209-222 and _anthropic_cache_settings() at runner.py:421-435 (anthropic_cache_instructions / anthropic_cache_tool_definitions). The plan's S1 (\"caching substrate at the shared runner seam (fidelity-neutral) — foundational\") and the Remediation \"S1 RESCOPED: cache the SYSTEM PROMPT (anthropic_cache_instructions/tool_definitions, anthropic-gated)... no RunRequest content-list change\" read as describing exactly what 0250 already shipped. Please clarify in the plan what S1 ADDS beyond 0250 (e.g. is it now a no-op verification, or a distinct piece such as cross-call cache-window TTL / breakpoint placement / metrics)? As written, S2/S3 are gated on S1 which may already be done — risking a redundant or under-specified foundational story."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782577185412475001,"uuid":"c5c308c9-4455-4620-a3c0-514628eb5ed6"}